article.headline: Buckeyes' Davenport, Matter combine for 32 points
article.linkText: Ohio State wins Buckeye Classic championship
article.story:
COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) -- Jessica Davenport scored 19 points and Caity Matter added 13 to lead Ohio State (No. 10 ESPN/USA Today, No. 11 AP) past Bradley 86-52 on Sunday to win the Buckeye Classic championship.

The Buckeyes (5-1) used a 19-2 run early in the second half and shot 63 percent from the field.

Davenport scored 17 of her 19 points in the first half, including a jumper with 10:02 left that gave Ohio State the lead for good at 22-20. Marcilla Packer and Stephanie Blanton each
scored 10 points for the Buckeyes.

Genny Mueller led Bradley (3-1) with 26 points and Jen Brown had 15.

The Buckeyes outscored Bradley 50-8 in the paint.
